Aircraft Sport.name: Aircraft Sport
Aircraft Sport.sportDescription: Air sports is not a single game but quite a vast sporting domain containing different aerial activities. Games which combine to make up the 'Air sports' include Air Racing, Aerobatics, Aeromodelling, Hang gliding, Human powered aircraft, Parachuting, Paragliding and Skydiving etc.

Archery.name: Archery
Archery.sportDescription: Competitive archery involves shooting arrows at a target for accuracy from a set distance or distances. The main forms of archery are Target Archery and Field Archery, and others include Clout Archery, 3D archery, Crossbow Archery, Flight Archery, and Ski Archery.

Athletics.name: Athletics
Athletics.tags: run, jump, sprint, discus, shotput, pole vault
Athletics.sportDescription: Commonly known as Track and Field, though it is an umbrella sport, which in addition to Track and Field it also comprises Cross Country Running, Road Running and Racewalking.

Australian Football.name: Australian Football
Australian Football.sportDescription: A fast paced football code from Australia, played between two teams of eighteen players on a large oval field. Six points are scored by kicking the ball between two tall goal posts, or one point for passing the ball either side of these. Alternative names are Australian Football, Aussie Rules, AFL, Australian Rules Football.

Badminton.name: Badminton
Badminton.sportDescription: An indoor game with rackets in which a shuttlecock is hit back and forth across a net.

Baseball.name: Baseball
Baseball.sportDescription: A bat and ball game in which the aim is to hit the ball and score runs by running around four bases.

Basketball.name: Basketball
Basketball.newTags: indoor, outdoor, team, ball sport, olympic
Basketball.sportDescription: Players attempt to shoot the ball through the hoop on the opponent’s court, moving the ball by throwing and dribbling.

Bicycle Motocross.name: Bicycle Motocross
Bicycle Motocross.sportDescription: A cycle sport which involves BMX bikes.

Billiards & Snooker.name: Billiards & Snooker
Billiards & Snooker.sportDescription: A cue sport played on a table covered with a green cloth with six pockets. It is played using a cue and 22 snooker balls: one white cue ball, 15 red balls and six balls of different colors. Points are awarded for using the cue ball to pot the red and colored balls.

Blind Sports.name: Blind Sports
Blind Sports.sportDescription: Blind Sports includes a wide variety of sport which are altered to support vision-impaired athletes.

Bocce.name: Bocce
Bocce.sportDescription: Is part of the boules sport family, similar to bowls and pétanque.

Boccia.name: Boccia
Boccia.sportDescription: A ball sport similar to bocce, bowls, and pétanque for athletes with physical disabilities.

Bowls.name: Bowls
Bowls.sportDescription: Commonly refers to Lawn Bowls. For other types of bowls sports, see Bowling.

Boxing.name: Boxing
Boxing.tags: jab, punch, block, ring, bell, fight, indoor
Boxing.newTags: indoor, individual, contact, combat sport, olympic
Boxing.sportDescription: A combat sport in which two players throw punches at each other.

Calisthenics.name: Calisthenics
Calisthenics.sportDescription: A competitive team sport in which athletes perform elements of rhythmic gymnastics and ballet.

Campdraft.name: Campdraft
Campdraft.sportDescription: A sport from Australia where a rider on horseback attempts to cut out a cattle from its herd and drive it into a pen.

Canoeing.name: Canoeing
Canoeing.newTags: outdoor, individual, team, water sport, olympic
Canoeing.sportDescription: Paddle sport in which the rider kneels or sits facing forward in a canoe.

Cricket.name: Cricket
Cricket.sportDescription: A team sport played on a rectangular pitch in the centre of a large grass oval, two batters protect their wicket while the fielding team try to get them out. Forms include Test, One-Day and T20.

Croquet.name: Croquet
Croquet.sportDescription: Players hit plastic or wooden balls using a mallet through hoops.

Curling.name: Curling
Curling.tags: sweep, push, ice, stones, bowls, target
Curling.sportDescription: Players slide stones on a sheet of ice towards the target area.

Cycling.name: Cycling
Cycling.sportDescription: There is a large range of sports involving riding a bicycle.

DanceSport.name: DanceSport
DanceSport.tags: art, theatre, ballroom, move, dress, suit
DanceSport.sportDescription: Dancesport is the competitive form of Ballroom and Latin Dancing, in which contestants perform dances before judges.

Darts.name: Darts
Darts.sportDescription: A throwing game in which small missiles are thrown at a target, which is called a dartboard.

Deaf Sports.name: Deaf Sports
Deaf Sports.sportDescription: Deaf Sports is inclusive of hearing-impaired and deaf athletes ranging through a variety of sports.

Disabled Wintersport.name: Disabled Wintersport
Disabled Wintersport.sportDescription: A range of winter sports from disabled athletes which includes Para-alpine, Para-snowboard and specialty sub discipline activities within each.

Diving.name: Diving
Diving.sportDescription: An aquatic sport where athletes dive into water from a raised launch pad, while performing acrobatic movements.

Dodgeball.name: Dodgeball
Dodgeball.sportDescription: Two teams throw balls at each other while trying to avoid the balls.

Dragon Boat.name: Dragon Boat
Dragon Boat.tags: canoe, row, paddle, water, boat, outdoor
Dragon Boat.sportDescription: A paddling sport using a long boat with many paddlers.

Eight Ball.name: Eight Ball
Eight Ball.tags: pool, billiards, table, shoot, stick, cue
Eight Ball.sportDescription: A cue sport, which is one of the most popular variants of pool, using 15 colored balls numbered from 1 to 15.

Disabled Riding.name: Disabled Riding
Disabled Riding.sportDescription: Equestrian sports including dressage, vaulting and carriage driving modified for disabled riders. Dressage is offered as a category at the Paralympics.
Disabled Riding.assocName: Riding for the Disabled Association of Australia

Equestrian.name: Equestrian
Equestrian.tags: horse, pony, trick, jump, ride, gallop, race
Equestrian.sportDescription: Competitions testing horse riding skills. Equestrian Vaulting is a gymnastics and dance discipline completed on horseback.

Pony Club.name: Pony Club
Pony Club.sportDescription: Junior equestrian horse riding skills including a gymnastics and dance discipline completed on horseback.

Fencing.name: Fencing
Fencing.tags: jab, suit, poke, sword, attack, defend
Fencing.sportDescription: Competitors face each other and attempt to touch each other with the tip of a thin sword.

Floorball.name: Floorball
Floorball.sportDescription: A type of floor hockey sport played indoors, popular in Nordic countries.

Flying Disc.name: Flying Disc
Flying Disc.sportDescription: Also known as Ultimate Frisbee, Flying Disc is played with a disc (frisbee), with points scored by passing the disc to a teammate in the opposing end zone.

Football (Soccer).name: Football (Soccer)
Football (Soccer).sportDescription: Around the world, Football mostly refers to Association Football, also known as Soccer in some places.

Futsal.name: Futsal
Futsal.sportDescription: Futsal is a variant of football (soccer), played on a smaller field usually indoors.

Gaelic Football.name: Gaelic Football
Gaelic Football.sportDescription: A type of football from Ireland with a goal similar to that used in rugby but having a net attached below the crossbar. The object is to kick or punch the round ball into the net (three points) or over the crossbar (one point).
Gaelic Football.assocName: Gaelic Football & Hurling Association of Australasia

Goalball.name: Goalball
Goalball.sportDescription: Goalball is a sport for vision-impaired athletes using a ball with bells with the aim of scoring in soccer-like nets.

Golf.name: Golf
Golf.tags: swing, putt, drive, hole, club, ball, buggy, bag
Golf.sportDescription: Players use a club to hit balls into a series of holes on a course, using the fewest number of strokes.

Gridiron.name: Gridiron
Gridiron.tags: throw, touchdown, american football, NFL, hutt-hutt, tackle, contact
Gridiron.sportDescription: The term used outside of the US for American Football.

Gymnastics.name: Gymnastics
Gymnastics.tags: floor, lift, jump, flip, land, aerobic, fitness
Gymnastics.sportDescription: A range of sports combining tumbling and acrobatic feats, usually done with apparatus. Two main sports: Rhythmic Gymnastics and Artistic Gymnastics.

Handball.name: Handball
Handball.newTags: indoor, team, contact, ball sport, olympic
Handball.sportDescription: A sport usually played indoors between teams of seven players, who pass a ball to throw it into the goal of the other team. Also known as Team Handball, Olympic Handball, European (Team) handball or Borden Ball.

Hockey.name: Hockey
Hockey.tags: hit, strike, ball, stick, goal, field, outdoor
Hockey.sportDescription: A large range of indoor and outdoor team sports which involves hitting a ball into a net. See Ice Hockey and Field Hockey.

Hurling.name: Hurling
Hurling.sportDescription: Hurling is a Gaelic outdoor team sport where players use a wooden stick to hit a ball between the opposing team's goalposts.
Hurling.assocName: Gaelic Football & Hurling Association of Australasia

Ice Hockey.name: Ice Hockey
Ice Hockey.tags: hit, puck, skate, pads, gear, rink, indoor
Ice Hockey.newTags: indoor, team, contact, ball sport, olympic
Ice Hockey.sportDescription: A contact sport which is played on ice while wearing skates and using a stick to hit a puck into a goal.

Ice Racing.name: Ice Racing
Ice Racing.sportDescription: Racing of motorized vehicles on predominantly natural ice surfaces like frozen lakes or rivers.

Ice Skating.name: Ice Skating
Ice Skating.tags: dance, synchronised, pairs, singles, artistic, theatre
Ice Skating.sportDescription: There is a range of sports that utilize ice skating, such as ice hockey, figure skating and speed skating.

Intellectual Impairment Sports.name: Intellectual Impairment Sports
Intellectual Impairment Sports.tags: inclusion, disability, able-bodied, non able bodied

Judo.name: Judo
Judo.tags: aikido, martial arts, karate, jujitsu, taekwondo
Judo.newTags: indoor, individual, contact, combat sport, olympic
Judo.sportDescription: The objective is to throw or takedown the opposing player to the ground.

Jujitsu.name: Jujitsu
Jujitsu.tags: aikido, martial arts, taekwondo, judo, karate
Jujitsu.sportDescription: A Japanese martial art using close combat for defeating an armed and armored opponent, with only a short weapon or none at all.

Karate.name: Karate
Karate.tags: aikido, martial arts, taekwondo, jujitsu, judo
Karate.sportDescription: A martial art developed in Japan which uses punching, kicking, knee strikes, elbow strikes, and some open-hand techniques.

Kendo.name: Kendo
Kendo.tags: aikido, martial arts, karate, jujitsu, judo, taekwondo
Kendo.sportDescription: A form of Japanese martial art that originated from kenjutsu, using bamboo swords and armour.

Kung Fu - Wushu.name: Kung Fu - Wushu
Kung Fu - Wushu.tags: aikido, martial arts, taekwondo, jujitsu, judo
Kung Fu - Wushu.sportDescription: A general term for Chinese martial arts, the competition format is Wushu.

Lacrosse.name: Lacrosse
Lacrosse.tags: contact, goal, net, carry, pass, catch, shoot, ball
Lacrosse.sportDescription: A team game, originally played by North American Indians, in which the ball is thrown, caught, and carried with a long-handled stick with a piece of shallow netting at one end.

Modern Pentathlon.name: Modern Pentathlon
Modern Pentathlon.tags: five, multiple, run, equestrian, shooting, swimming, fencing

Motor Sport.name: Motor Sport
Motor Sport.tags: race, car, outdoor, time, track, speedway, course
Motor Sport.sportDescription: Includes a wide range of sports, each linked with its use of a motor to propel a driver, and all have an element of thrill and danger for the driver and spectator.
Motor Sport.assocName: Confederation of Australian Motor Sport Ltd (CAMS)

Motorcycling.name: Motorcycling
Motorcycling.tags: cross, bike, dirt, race, time, track, course
Motorcycling.sportDescription: A motorcycle sport involving racing motorcycles as teams or individuals around a circular track. At the elite level it is in the form of MotoGP racing. Also known as Moto racing and Bike racing.

Mountain Bike.name: Mountain Bike
Mountain Bike.tags: cross, bike, dirt, race, time, track, course
Mountain Bike.sportDescription: Held on steep and rough terrain, involving jumps, rock gardens, and other obstacles.

Muaythai.name: Muaythai
Muaythai.tags: aikido, martial arts, taekwondo, jujitsu, judo
Muaythai.sportDescription: A full contact fighting sport in which fighters try to defeat their opponents by using different techniques that make use of fists, elbows, knees, and shins.

Netball.name: Netball
Netball.sportDescription: A team game with seven players on a side, similar to basketball except that players are restricted to certain sections of the court, and a player receiving the ball must stand still until they have passed it to another player.

Orienteering.name: Orienteering
Orienteering.tags: find, run, discover, map, cross-country, flags
Orienteering.sportDescription: Participants find their way to various checkpoints across rough country with the aid of a map and compass, the winner being the one with the lowest elapsed time.

Outrigger Canoeing.name: Outrigger Canoeing
Outrigger Canoeing.newTags: outdoor, individual, team, water sport, olympic
Outrigger Canoeing.sportDescription: Racing using a type of canoe featuring one or more lateral support floats known as outriggers, which are fastened to one or both sides of the main hull.
Outrigger Canoeing.assocName: Australian Outrigger Canoe Racing Association Inc

Petanque.name: Petanque
Petanque.sportDescription: A type of boules in which the objective is to throw hollow metal balls towards a small wooden target ball.

Polo.name: Polo
Polo.tags: horse, stick, ride, pony, mallet, ball
Polo.sportDescription: (Horse Polo) — a team sport played on horseback in which the objective is to hit a ball into a goal using a long-handled mallet.

Polocrosse.name: Polocrosse
Polocrosse.tags: racquet, net, lacrosse, horse, pony, stick, ball
Polocrosse.sportDescription: An equestrian sport combining the sports of lacrosse and polo.

Powerlifting.name: Powerlifting
Powerlifting.tags: squat, bench press, deadlift, strength, weights
Powerlifting.sportDescription: Tests of strength on three lifts: dead lift, bench press and squat.

Roller Sports.name: Roller Sports
Roller Sports.tags: artistic, skating, inline, hockey, derby, skateboarding, speed
Roller Sports.sportDescription: Roller sports comprises a range of sports where competitors wear roller skaters including Roller Derby, Inline Hockey, Artistic, Speed, Roller Hockey, Skateboarding

Rowing.name: Rowing
Rowing.newTags: outdoor, individual, team, water sport, olympic
Rowing.sportDescription: A sport in which competitors propel a boat using oars.

Rugby League.name: Rugby League
Rugby League.tags: try, pass, kick, conversion, tacke, contact
Rugby League.sportDescription: A rough game involving tackling the players in a bid to get the ball, with each team attempting to carry it over the end line.

Rugby Union.name: Rugby Union
Rugby Union.tags: try, pass, kick, conversion, tacke, scrum, contact
Rugby Union.newTags: outdoor, team, contact, ball sport, olympic
Rugby Union.sportDescription: Played on a grass field by two opposing teams with two H-shaped goalposts at opposite ends.

Sailing / Yachting.name: Sailing / Yachting
Sailing / Yachting.tags: yacht, boat, kite, sails, wind, surfing
Sailing / Yachting.newTags: outdoor, individual, team, water sport, olympic
Sailing / Yachting.sportDescription: A sport that involves moving a boat by using the power of the wind.

Snow Sports.name: Snow Sports
Snow Sports.sportDescription: Comprises of Alpine Skiing, Cross Country Skiing, Freestyle Skiing, Snowboarding, Para-alpine, Para-snowboard and specialty sub discipline activities within each.

Shooting.name: Shooting
Shooting.sportDescription: Many events involving shooting at targets using guns like pistols and rifles.

Softball.name: Softball
Softball.sportDescription: There are three styles of softball: fast pitch, "modified" fast pitch, and slow pitch.

Sport Climbing.name: Sport Climbing
Sport Climbing.tags: rock, hand, feet, ascend, lift, body, object, steep, outdoor
Sport Climbing.sportDescription: Sports rock climbing competitions can be Lead Climbing, Speed Climbing or Bouldering.

Squash.name: Squash
Squash.tags: rubber, ball, four-wall, raquet, glasses, singles, doubles, indoor
Squash.sportDescription: A racquet sport played by two or four players in a four-walled court with a small hollow rubber ball.

Surf Life Saving.name: Surf Life Saving
Surf Life Saving.tags: swim, canoe, body, board, rescue, water, outdoor
Surf Life Saving.sportDescription: Competitions consist of performing various tasks performed by lifeguards on the beach.

Surfing.name: Surfing
Surfing.sportDescription: Participants stand on a surfboard, and use the waves for propulsion.

Swimming.name: Swimming
Swimming.newTags: indoor, outdoor, individual, team, water sport, olympic
Swimming.sportDescription: Swimming the sport of propelling oneself through water using four main techniques of freestyle, backstroke, breathstroke and butterfly.

Synchronised Swimming.name: Synchronised Swimming
Synchronised Swimming.newTags: indoor, outdoor, team, water sport, olympic
Synchronised Swimming.sportDescription: In Synchronised Swimming athletes perform synchronized dance routines to music whilst in water.

Table Tennis.name: Table Tennis
Table Tennis.tags: bat, hit, forehand, backhand, ball, net, table, doubles, singles
Table Tennis.newTags: indoor, individual, team, ball sport, olympic
Table Tennis.sportDescription: (also called Ping Pong) — a racket sport played with small paddles and a lightweight ball on a rectangular table with a net in the middle.

Taekwondo.name: Taekwondo
Taekwondo.newTags: indoor, individual, contact, combat sport, olympic
Taekwondo.sportDescription: Taekwondo is a self-defense discipline that originated in Korea.

Tennis.name: Tennis
Tennis.tags: racquet, hit, forehand, backhand, ball, net, table, doubles, singles
Tennis.newTags: outdoor, individual, team, ball sport, olympic
Tennis.sportDescription: Tennis is a court sport where players use a stringed racket to hit a ball to each other over a net.

Tenpin Bowling.name: Tenpin Bowling
Tenpin Bowling.tags: pins, balls, holes, score, lane, spin, strike, indoor
Tenpin Bowling.sportDescription: Tenpin Bowling is a sport where a competitor rolls a bowling ball on to a wooden or synthetic lane to knock down pins.

Touch.name: Touch
Touch.sportDescription: A team sport derived from Rugby Football, in which the tackling is replaced with just a touch.

Transplant.name: Transplant
Transplant.sportDescription: Transplant sports are for organ transplant recepients and includes various sports for eligible competitors.

Triathlon.name: Triathlon
Triathlon.tags: swimming, cycling, running, water, ride, bike, multiple
Triathlon.sportDescription: Triathlon is a race consisting of three events, usually swimming, cycling, and running in consecutive order.

Underwater Sports.name: Underwater Sports
Underwater Sports.tags: snorkelling, apnoea, free diving, scuba, fin swimming, spearfishing, hockey, rugby
Underwater Sports.newTags: indoor, outdoor, individual, team, water sports
Underwater Sports.sportDescription: Underwater Sports includes a variety of sports where competitors wear scuba gear and includes underwater rugby, hockey and fin swimming.

Volleyball.name: Volleyball
Volleyball.tags: net, block, dig, set, spike, serve, hands
Volleyball.newTags: indoor, outdoor, team, ball sport, olympic
Volleyball.sportDescription: Volleyball is a game for two teams of six players, in which a large ball is hit by hand over a high net, the aim being to score points by making the ball reach the ground on the opponent's side of the court. See also Beach Volleyball.

Water Polo.name: Water Polo
Water Polo.newTags: indoor, outdoor, team, ball sport, water sport, olympic
Water Polo.sportDescription: Water Polo is a team sport played in swimming pools, the aim is to pass the ball over the water and into the goal net.

Water Skiing.name: Water Skiing
Water Skiing.tags: race, board, water, ski, wake, show, barefoot, outdoor
Water Skiing.sportDescription: Competitors are pulled along behind a boat skimming atop the water wearing one or two skis.

Weightlifting.name: Weightlifting
Weightlifting.sportDescription: Weightlifting competitors attempt to lift weights mounted on barbells above their head in the techniques of Clean & Jerk and Snatch.

Wheelchair Sports.name: Wheelchair Sports
Wheelchair Sports.tags: adaptive, archery, afl, surfing, mountain biking, boccia, canoe, cycling, football, hockey, paratriathlon, lawn bowls,
Wheelchair Sports.newTags: indoor, outdoor, individual, team, ball sport, disability, olympic
Wheelchair Sports.sportDescription: Wheelchair sports includes a variety of sports tailored for athletes with physical impairment using modified wheelchairs.

Wrestling.name: Wrestling
Wrestling.tags: combat, grappling, throws, takedowns, pins, joint-locks
Wrestling.newTags: indoor, individual, team, contact, combat sport, olympic
Wrestling.sportDescription: Wrestling is a combat sport between two competitors involving grappling type techniques. Popular forms include the Olympic styles of Greco-Roman and Freestyle.
